see Nick Menere and https://jdog.atlassian.com/browse/JRADEV-6535

The MultiSelectSearcher cannot be created using plugins 2.0. It has a dependency on:
# {{ComponentLocator}}
# {{ComponentFactory}} 
which we do no expose in plugins 2.0.

The workaround is to implement the plugin as a plugins 1.0 plugin.

The [custom field plugin documentation|http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/qNoB] suggests that people should be able to reuse our searchers for their own custom field types. We may need to check that all our searchers are available via plugin 2.0.

