The XML view of the issue navigator is expensive. In some cases it can render the server non-operational. There's a knowledge base article describing the problem (and how to limit it) here:

http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/twCzD

In the labels dialogue, if the user attempts to add more than 20 labels at a time to an issue, it displays an error message:
{noformat}
There was a problem updating the issue's labels. Please check if you are logged in and have the permissions to edit the issue.
{noformat}
There is no indication that it is the number of labels that is the real cause of the failure.

